definitions.definition: The application of rituals or actions, especially those based on occult knowledge, to subdue or manipulate natural or supernatural beings and forces in order to have some benefit from them.

subdefinitions.definition: The supernatural forces which are drawn on in such a ritual.
A specific ritual or procedure associated with such magic; a spell ; a magical ability.
The ability to cast a magic spell.
examples: I learned a new magic after rescuing the tree fairy.

definitions.definition: Something producing successful and remarkable results, especially when not fully understood; an enchanting quality; exceptional skill.

subdefinitions.definition: Complicated or esoteric code that is not expected to be generally understood.

definitions.definition: The art or practice of performing conjuring tricks and illusions to give the appearance of supernatural phenomena or powers.

subdefinitions.definition: One such conjuring trick or illusion.

main_definition: The application of rituals or actions, especially those based on occult knowledge, to subdue or manipulate natural or supernatural beings and forces in order to have some benefit from them. [from 14th c.]
secondary_definitions: Something producing successful and remarkable results, especially when not fully understood; an enchanting quality; exceptional skill. [from 17th c.]
( entertainment ) The art or practice of performing conjuring tricks and illusions to give the appearance of supernatural phenomena or powers.
